PostgreSQL on AWS whitepaper - https://media.amazonwebservices.com/AWS_RDBMS_PostgreSQL.pdf


The main tuning parameter for PostgreSQL -  
Ref : https://www.enterprisedb.com/postgres-tutorials/comprehensive-guide-how-tune-database-parameters-and-configuration-postgresql

1. shared_buffer - This parameter sets how much dedicated memory will be used by PostgreSQL for the cache

2. wal_buffers

3. effective_cache_size

4. work_mem

5. synchronous_commit

6. max_connections

7. max_prepared_transactions

8. max_worker_processes

9. max_parallel_workers_per_gather - The maximum workers a Gather or GatherMerge node can use

10. max_parallel_workers

11. effective_io_concurrency

12. random_page_cost

13. min_ and max_wal_size

14. max_fsm_pages



Autovacuum internal - https://www.percona.com/blog/2018/08/10/tuning-autovacuum-in-postgresql-and-autovacuum-internals/

